{"in": {"title": "Problemscape", "subtitle": "<span id=\"tr_lore_id\">teacherless</span>", "lines": ["JINGA: I haven't seen you before. Are you visiting someone?", "PLAYER: I'm looking for my teacher.", "JINGA: Oh you're looking for your teacher! I'm looking for my teacher too. She is an Xpert.", "JINGA: You see, Xperts are good at math and are also the teachers in Arithma.", "JINGA: I'm trying to become an Xpert myself! I was learning math from my teacher until he disappeared! Poof! Vanished!", "PLAYER: Vanished? What do you mean?", "JINGA: Yes! Vanished! Disappeared! The mayor thinks all the teachers have been kidnapped by PiRats!", "PLAYER: I'm worried. Is the mayor doing something about it?", "JINGA: No! The mayor has been very hard to find since the Xperts disappeared! I'm going to go and look for my teacher myself.", "JINGA: Do you want to come with me? We can look for my teacher and your teacher together!", "PLAYER: Can we go and talk to the mayor first?", "JINGA: Alright, let's go find the mayor. He might give us some clues. Before we start, I have to tell you something!", "JINGA: Arithma is in big trouble! No one here can do any math. We'll see many Arithmans who need our help!", "PLAYER: How can there be a nation where no one can do math?", "JINGA: We have Xperts and Mathers who can do math! But they've all vanished!", "JINGA: The reason most of us can't do math is that Arithmans are scared of math! How about you? Are you scared of math?", "PLAYER: No, I know I can learn when I don't know how to do something.", "JINGA: Oh yay!! To tell you the truth, I am a little scared of math. Whenever my teacher gives me a problem to solve, I get worried about whether I can solve it.", "JINGA: My teacher always says that learning and practicing are the best ways to lose fear of math. I want to learn from you so that I never get scared of solving problems."], "speaker_map": {"NARRATOR": "Matthew", "SCENE": "Matthew", "TITLE": "Joanna", "SMALL VOICE": "Raveena", "FANGS":